  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p><span style=\"font-family:Roboto, sans-serif\">Whether you're using magic items, wielding innate magic, or dabbling in spellcasting, you can sneak spells past your foes' defenses as easily as any blade. When you succeed at a spell attack roll against an </span>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.AJh5ex99aV6VTggg]{Off-Guard}<span style=\"font-family:Roboto, sans-serif\"> foe's AC and the spell deals damage, you </span>deal an extra 1d6 precision damage. <span style=\"font-family:Roboto, sans-serif\">If your single spell leads to multiple separate damage rolls, apply your sneak attack damage only once per target.</span></p><p>As your eldritch shadow level increases, so does the number of damage dice for your sneak attack. Increase the number of dice by one at 5th, 11th, and 17th levels.</p>"
    },
